onReport.t.sol
├── when call is reentrant
│  └── it should revert with ReentrancyGuardReentrantCall
└── when call is not reentrant
   ├── when caller is the CRE forwarder 
   │  ├── when the provided metadata is invalid
   │  │  └── it should revert
   │  └── when the provided metadata is valid
   │     ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a chain that is not a registered spoke chain
   │     │  └── it should revert with InvalidChainId
   │     └── when all provided snapshots reference a chain that is a registered spoke chain
   │        ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a mailbox address that is not the one registered for the given spoke chain
   │        │  └── it should revert with InvalidChainId
   │        └── when all provided snapshots reference the registered mailbox address for the given spoke chain
   │           ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a block timestamp that exceeds the current chain timestamp by more than the max future tolerance
   │           │  └── it should revert with FutureSnapshot
   │           └── when all provided snapshots reference a block timestamp that does not exceed the current chain timestamp by more than the max future tolerance
   │              ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a block timestamp that is either older than current stored snapshot or which age exceeds the max caliber staleness threshold
   │              │  └── it should revert with StaleSnapshot
   │              └── when all provided snapshots reference a block timestamp that is newer than current stored snapshot and which age is lower than the max caliber staleness threshold
   │                 └── it should update the accounting data for all given spoke chains
   └── when caller is not the CRE forwarder
      ├── when caller is not the Security Council
      │  └── it should revert with UnauthorizedCaller
      └── when caller is the Security Council
         ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a chain that is not a registered spoke chain
         │  └── it should revert with InvalidChainId
         └── when all provided snapshots reference a chain that is a registered spoke chain
            ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a mailbox address that is not the one registered for the given spoke chain
            │  └── it should revert with InvalidChainId
            └── when all provided snapshots reference the registered mailbox address for the given spoke chain
               ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a block timestamp that exceeds the current chain timestamp by more than the max future tolerance
               │  └── it should revert with FutureSnapshot
               └── when all provided snapshots reference a block timestamp that does not exceed the current chain timestamp by more than the max future tolerance
                  ├── when one of the provided snapshots references a block timestamp that is either older than current stored snapshot or which age exceeds the max caliber staleness threshold
                  │  └── it should revert with StaleSnapshot
                  └── when all provided snapshots reference a block timestamp that is newer than current stored snapshot and which age is lower than the max caliber staleness threshold
                     └── it should update the accounting data for all given spoke chains
